  "texts": [
    "An SL n (C)-Higgs bundle is stable if the inequality is strict for all E ′, and it is polystable if it is semistable and it splits as a direct sum of stable bundles (all of degree 0).There is a more general notion of polystability for G-Higgs bundles that makes the non-abelian Hodge correspondence true for general connected real reductive Lie groups; see [GPGiR12, Definition 2.9].",
    "However, it turns out that for linear groups, this is equivalent [AABC + 19, Proposition 2.10] to polystability for Higgs vector bundles defined above: Proposition 4.7.",
    "Let G be a linear real reductive Lie group.",
    "A G-Higgs bundle (P, Φ) is polystable if and only if the associated Higgs vector bundle is polystable.We then have the following non-abelian Hodge correspondence.",
    "This was proved by Hitchin [Hit87] and Donaldson [Don87] for SL 2 (C), by Simpson [Sim88] and Corlette [Cor88] for complex reductive groups, and by García-Prada-Gothen-Mundet I Riera [GPGiR12] for connected real reductive groups.Theorem 4.8 (Non-abelian Hodge correspondence)."
  ],
